-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-19/rinascente-s-borletti-examines-bid-backed-by-lvmh-stampa-says.html
La Rinascente SpA Chairman Maurizio Borletti received backing from  LVMH Moet Hennessy Louis Vuitton
SA  to prepare a bid for the Italian department-store chain, La
Stampa reported.  Borletti, whose family holds 4 percent of the company that
owns 97 percent of La Rinascente, has been granted access to
information on the company, according to an e-mailed statement
late yesterday.    Tamburi Investment Partners SpA  is also backing the
potential bid, according to daily newspaper Stampa. The
investors have until the end of the month to review the
information, the newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Elisa Martinuzzi in Milan at 
 emartinuzzi@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
